      <h1 class="teal">Who does America trade with? How should we decide who to trade with, and what to trade?</h1><br>
      
      <p>Foreign trade of the United States comprises the international imports and exports of the United States, one of the world&#39;s most significant economic markets. The country is among the top three global importers and exporters.</p>
      <p>The regulation of trade is constitutionally vested in the United States Congress. After the Great Depression, the country emerged as among the most significant global trade policy-makers, and it is now a partner to a number of international trade agreements, including the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) and the International Trade Organization(ITO). Gross U.S. assets held by foreigners were $16.3 trillion as of the end of 2006 (over 100% of GDP).</p><br>

