         <li>What kinds of products do I use regularly?&nbsp;Where do these products come from? Are they being produced ethically?</li>
         <li>How do trade embargoes set by the US affect everyday commodity prices for regular individuals like myself?&nbsp;If the US is such a great advocate of free trade, should it continue to use trade embargoes as a way to threaten other nations for actions it does not necessarily agree with? Are we as a nation being hypocritical?</li>
         <li>What stance do the 2016 candidates have on foreign trade, or do they even have any?&nbsp;Note: it is critical for you as a citizen to be in coherence with the candidates on the issue of trade, as it is what drives the country&rsquo;s GDP in a huge way, and therefore also helps solve the problem of accumulating debt.</li>
         <li>Do citizens of another country deserve to have an economy suffer just because the U.S. has a different government than them?&nbsp;Or is the threat of communism and other types of government so extreme that we should avoid dealing with it?</li>
      </ul><br>

